description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Employer: Torbay and South Devon NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;37.5 hrs per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Salary £38,890-£44,503 plus EDC&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Mid-Grade Clinical Pharmacist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a pharmacist looking to further develop your clinical and leadership skills? Are you looking to join a supportive, friendly pharmacy team? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen to join the pharmacy team at Torbay and South Devon NHS Foundation Trust. This post is part of our mid-grade pharmacists’ programme, which includes specialist clinical roles in admissions, surgery and medicine as well as providing to develop core senior skills including prescribing, education and leadership. Leading and developing our foundation pharmacist-led weekend clinical service, this job would suit a pharmacist with excellent clinical knowledge, who is keen to develop their leadership qualities.  Further clinical and quality improvement skills will also be required in aiding the senior pharmacist team to develop and implement new services and processes, both in response to COVID-19 and as part of STP and local initiatives. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;At ward level, you will work closely with consultants and ward-based staff, providing pharmaceutical expertise to ensure the safety of patients. You will be responsible for helping to mentor both foundation pharmacists and pre-registration pharmacists, and will be given opportunities to gain experience in medicines optimisation, discharge facilitation, education and training, leadership and rota co-ordination.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The well-established,  friendly and innovative clinical pharmacy service at Torbay is based on excellent ward level integration and team working between senior and mid-grade specialist pharmacists, foundation pharmacists and ward based medicines optimisation technicians and assistants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should ideally have completed, or be nearing completion of a postgraduate diploma in clinical pharmacy, and will be supported to undertake a prescribing qualification if they do not already hold one. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you think this sounds like a job you would be interested in, we would welcome your application. For an informal discussion about the role, please contact Jane Pyle, Clinical Pharmacy Manager &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;jane.pyle@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
